  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Steel triple innominate osteotomy was designed for dysplastic hip in adolescents and young
      adults with three incisions to increase the coverage; however the amount of correction
      remained questionable due to ligamentous attachments that hinder the rotation. The
      investigators modified the technique with two anterior incisions and ramus cuts close to
      inferior acetabulum. The purpose of this study is to compare these two techniques in femoral
      head coverage
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
