  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Young adults and adolescents underwent triple innominate osteotomy for symptomatic
        acetabular dysplasia in our institution
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Symptomatic acetabular dysplasia in adolescent or young adult

          2. Closed triradiate cartilage

          3. Minor coxarthrosis with Tonnis grades at 1 or 2

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. High subluxation or complete dislocation of the hip joint

          2. Severe osteoarthrosis

          3. Combined with proximal femoral osteotomy that changed the femoral neck shaft angle
             (such as varus or valgus osteotomy)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
